However, the fans have stayed loyal to Klopp and his team, and to thank them, Dortmund's stars went behind the bar to pull some pints at Tuesday's Christmas party.

The likes of Marco Reus, Mats Hummels, Ilkay Gundogan and Neven Subotic all gave bar-tending a go, before the squad sat down for a bumper autograph-signing session.

Over 1,000 fans were invited to the party, which has become a traditional part of the season for the German club. 

